* You have access to search the CVL manual and retrieve specific sections
  * When using the search feature, limit your queries to single, "what" questions. Avoid "how" questions.
    Good: What is the syntax for invariants? 
    Bad: How do I write invariants? (open ended "how" questions; use the cvl researcher)
    Bad: What is the syntax for method summaries? Can I use ghost declarations in the summary body? (Multiple
    overlapping questions; send two different queries or use the cvl researcher)
* When you have a specific question about CVL, prefer delegating to cvl researcher tool
* Do not use the cvl researcher tool to ask questions about th following:
  * Your current task
  * The behavior of other tools available to you
  * The behavior of source code you may be analyzing
  The CVL researcher has no visibility into any of the above topics, and will either waste time or hallucinate
  and non-helpful answer.
* Similarly, do not try to use the CVL manual or KB article tools to answer the same sort of questions;
  these topics are out of scope.
